Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_proto_model(25.10)                            report_proto_model(25.10)

Name
       report_proto_model - Reports statistics information for models

Syntax
       report_proto_model

       [-help]

       [-constraint]

       [-file <string>]

       [-min_inst <integer> | -identified | -created]

       [-min_inst <integer>]

       [-instance_ratio <float> | -min_inst <integer>]

       Reports statistics information for models.

       Note:  The  report_proto_model command takes the top-level cells in ac-
       count while reporting the netlist reduction ratio at the end.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each report_proto_model parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man report_proto_model

       -constraint
              Report physical constraint information.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -created
              Reports  the statistics, including reduction ratio of the models
              that have been created.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -file <string>
              Specifies output report file name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -identified
              Reports the statistics of the modules/instgroups that have  been
              identified as models.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -instance_ratio <float>
              Specifies  ratio  value  where  report_proto_model  only reports
              flexModels that have instance ratio greater  than  or  equal  to
              this specified value.

              Min: 0

              Max: 1.79769313486232e+308

              Data_type: float, optional

       -min_inst <integer>
              Specifies  the  threshold  of  an instance count that is used to
              filter modules.

              Data_type: int, optional

Examples
              * The following command reports modules or instance groups  have
                been identified as FlexModels

                report_proto_model -identified

              * The  following command reports models in the design with hier-
                archical modules that have at least 30 instances:

                report_proto_model -min_inst 30

              * The following command reports all models after the  FlexModels
                have been committed:

                report_proto_model -created

              * If  -constraint  option  is  specified, the report has the has
                PhysicalConstraint column

                report_proto_model -created

                report_proto_model -created -constraint

Related Information
              *

                set_proto_model

              *

                Prototyping Methodologies chapter in the Innovus User Guide

